Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 122, 6 or 181, 37. Name Aristeidas. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, 0321.32.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0623)
